## Special Note on the EDU Formula

The EDU Formula: EDU(A,X) = (A/255·π), (406.4/X)

This mathematical discovery is made freely available to the scientific community
for research and educational purposes. While the software implementation is under
MIT license, commercial applications of the EDU Formula should acknowledge:

"Based on the EDU Formula discovered by Eduard Terre (ASCII-EDU), Offenburg, Germany, 2024"

The formula itself cannot be patented as it represents a mathematical truth,
but we request proper attribution in academic and commercial uses.